swL2MgmtMIB.name: swL2MgmtMIB

swL2MgmtMIB.description: The Structure of Common Management Information for making a trunk and IGMP related function for D-Link devices.

swL2DevInfoFrontPanelLedStatus.name: swL2DevInfoFrontPanelLedStatus
swL2DevInfoFrontPanelLedStatus.description: This object is a set of system LED indications. The two octets is defined as system LED. The first LED is power LED. The second LED is console LED. The other octets following the second octets are the logical port LED (following dot1dBasePort ordering). Every two bytes are presented to a port. The first byte is presentd to the Link/Activity LED. The second byte is presented to the Speed LED. Link/Activity LED : The most significant bit is used for blink/solid: 8 = The LED blinks. The second significant bit is used for link status: 1 = link fail. 2 = link pass. Speed LED : 01 = 10Mbps. 02 = 100Mbps. 03 = 1000Mbps. The four remaining bits are currently unused and must be 0.

swL2Module_1_Type.name: swL2Module_1_Type
swL2Module_1_Type.description: This object indicates the module type.

swL2Module_2_Type.name: swL2Module_2_Type
swL2Module_2_Type.description: This object indicates the module type.

swL2CPUutilizationIn5sec.name: swL2CPUutilizationIn5sec
swL2CPUutilizationIn5sec.description: Time scale is 5 seconds.The value will be between 0%(idle) and 100% (very busy).

swL2CPUutilizationIn1min.name: swL2CPUutilizationIn1min
swL2CPUutilizationIn1min.description: Time scale is 1 minute.The value will be between 0%(idle) and 100% (very busy).

swL2CPUutilizationIn5min.name: swL2CPUutilizationIn5min
swL2CPUutilizationIn5min.description: Time scale is 5 minute.The value will be between 0%(idle) and 100% (very busy).

swL2DevAlarmLinkChange.name: swL2DevAlarmLinkChange
swL2DevAlarmLinkChange.description: This object determines whether or not to send a trap message when the link changes. If the object is enabled (3), the Link Change trap is sent by the device when any of its port links change. The device does not send the trap if this object value is disabled or in another state.

swL2DevCtrlSystemReboot.name: swL2DevCtrlSystemReboot
swL2DevCtrlSystemReboot.description: This object indicates the agent system reboot state. The agent always returns other(1) when this object is read.

swL2DevCtrlSubnetMask.name: swL2DevCtrlSubnetMask
swL2DevCtrlSubnetMask.description: This object indicates system subnet mask.

swL2DevCtrlDefaultGateway.name: swL2DevCtrlDefaultGateway
swL2DevCtrlDefaultGateway.description: This object indicates system default gateway.

swL2DevCtrlManagementVlanId.name: swL2DevCtrlManagementVlanId
swL2DevCtrlManagementVlanId.description: This object controls which Vlan includes system ip. And the Vlan should have been created.

swL2DevCtrlStpState.name: swL2DevCtrlStpState
swL2DevCtrlStpState.description: This object can be enabled or disabled spanning tree algorithm during runtime of the system.

swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping.name: swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping
swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping.description: This object indicates layer 2 Internet Group Management Protocol (IGMP) capture function is enabled or disabled .

swL2DevCtrlCleanAllStatisticCounter.name: swL2DevCtrlCleanAllStatisticCounter
swL2DevCtrlCleanAllStatisticCounter.description: As the object is set to active, all the statistic counters will be cleared. If set to normal, do nothing.

swL2DevCtrlSnmpEnableAuthenTraps.name: swL2DevCtrlSnmpEnableAuthenTraps
swL2DevCtrlSnmpEnableAuthenTraps.description: Indicates whether the SNMP entity is permitted to generate authenticationFailure traps. The value of this object overrides any configuration information; as such, it provides a means whereby all authenticationFailure traps may be disabled. Note that it is strongly recommended that this object be stored in non-volatile memory so that it remains constant across re-initializations of the network management system.

swL2DevCtrlRmonState.name: swL2DevCtrlRmonState
swL2DevCtrlRmonState.description: This object can be enabled or disabled RMON.

swL2DevCtrlIpAutoConfig.name: swL2DevCtrlIpAutoConfig
swL2DevCtrlIpAutoConfig.description: Indicates the status of automatically getting configuration from TFTP server on device

swL2PortCtrlMulticastfilter.name: swL2PortCtrlMulticastfilter
swL2PortCtrlMulticastfilter.description: This object decide the multicast packets filtering mode on all port .

swL2MACNotifyState.name: swL2MACNotifyState
swL2MACNotifyState.description: This object can enabled or disabled MAC Notification.

swL2MACNotifyHistorySize.name: swL2MACNotifyHistorySize
swL2MACNotifyHistorySize.description: This object indicates the history size of variation MAC in address table. The default value is 1 .

swL2MACNotifyInterval.name: swL2MACNotifyInterval
swL2MACNotifyInterval.description: This object indicates the time interval in second for trigger the MAC notify message.

swL2DevCtrlVLANTrunkState.name: swL2DevCtrlVLANTrunkState
swL2DevCtrlVLANTrunkState.description: This indicates the global state of the VLAN trunking feature of the device.

swL2DevCtrlLLDPState.name: swL2DevCtrlLLDPState
swL2DevCtrlLLDPState.description: Specifies the state of the LLDP function. When this function is enabled, the switch can start to transmit LLDP packets and receive and process the LLDP packets. The specific function of each port will depend on the per port LLDP setting. For the advertisement of LLDP packets, the switch announces the information to its neighbor through ports. For receiving LLDP packets, the switch will learn the information from the LLDP packets advertised from the neighbor in the neighbor table.

swL2DevCtrlLLDPForwardMessageState.name: swL2DevCtrlLLDPForwardMessageState
swL2DevCtrlLLDPForwardMessageState.description: When lldp is disabled and lldp forward_message's are enabled, the LLDP Data Unit packets received by the switch will be forwarded.

swL2DevCtrlVlanIdOfFDBTbl.name: swL2DevCtrlVlanIdOfFDBTbl
swL2DevCtrlVlanIdOfFDBTbl.description: Indicates the VLAN ID to which the Dot1dTpFdbTable belongs; The default value is DEFAULT_VLAN_ID of the system.

swL2PortInfoTable.name: swL2PortInfoTable
swL2PortInfoTable.description: A table that contains information about every port.

swL2PortInfoEntry.name: swL2PortInfoEntry
swL2PortInfoEntry.description: A list of information for each port of the device.

swL2PortInfoPortIndex.name: swL2PortInfoPortIndex
swL2PortInfoPortIndex.description: This object indicates the module's port number.(1..Max port number in the module)

swL2PortInfoLinkStatus.name: swL2PortInfoLinkStatus
swL2PortInfoLinkStatus.description: This object indicates the port link status.

swL2PortInfoNwayStatus.name: swL2PortInfoNwayStatus
swL2PortInfoNwayStatus.description: This object indicates the port speed and duplex mode.

swL2PortCtrlTable.name: swL2PortCtrlTable
swL2PortCtrlTable.description: A table that contains control information about every port.

swL2PortCtrlEntry.name: swL2PortCtrlEntry
swL2PortCtrlEntry.description: A list of control information for each port of the device.

swL2PortCtrlPortIndex.name: swL2PortCtrlPortIndex
swL2PortCtrlPortIndex.description: This object indicates the module's port number.(1..Max port number in the module)

swL2PortCtrlAdminState.name: swL2PortCtrlAdminState
swL2PortCtrlAdminState.description: This object decide the port enabled or disabled.

swL2PortCtrlNwayState.name: swL2PortCtrlNwayState
swL2PortCtrlNwayState.description: Chose the port speed, duplex mode, and N-Way function mode.

swL2PortCtrlFlowCtrlState.name: swL2PortCtrlFlowCtrlState
swL2PortCtrlFlowCtrlState.description: Set flow control function as enabled or disabled.

swL2PortCtrlDescription.name: swL2PortCtrlDescription
swL2PortCtrlDescription.description: The object describe the ports in text.

swL2PortCtrlMACNotifyState.name: swL2PortCtrlMACNotifyState
swL2PortCtrlMACNotifyState.description: This object set each poet MAC notification state.

swL2PortCtrlMDIXState.name: swL2PortCtrlMDIXState
swL2PortCtrlMDIXState.description: This object controls the MDIX state of a specified port.

swL2PortErrTable.name: swL2PortErrTable
swL2PortErrTable.description: A table that contains information about Err port.

swL2PortErrEntry.name: swL2PortErrEntry
swL2PortErrEntry.description: A list of information for err port of the device.

swL2PortErrPortIndex.name: swL2PortErrPortIndex
swL2PortErrPortIndex.description: This object indicates the module's port number.(1..Max port number in the module)

swL2PortErrPortState.name: swL2PortErrPortState
swL2PortErrPortState.description: This object decide the portstate enabled or disabled.

swL2PortErrPortStatus.name: swL2PortErrPortStatus
swL2PortErrPortStatus.description: This object decide the PortStatus whether err-disabled.

swL2PortErrPortReason.name: swL2PortErrPortReason
swL2PortErrPortReason.description: This object decide the PortStatus STP LBD or Storm control.

swL2PortErrDescription.name: swL2PortErrDescription
swL2PortErrDescription.description: The object describe the ports in text.

swL2QOSBandwidthControlEntry.name: swL2QOSBandwidthControlEntry
swL2QOSBandwidthControlEntry.description: A list of information contained in swL2QOSBandwidthControlTable.

swL2QOSBandwidthRxRate.name: swL2QOSBandwidthRxRate
swL2QOSBandwidthRxRate.description: Indicates RX Rate(Kbit/sec) of the specifed port.Value 1024000 means no limit.

swL2QOSBandwidthTxRate.name: swL2QOSBandwidthTxRate
swL2QOSBandwidthTxRate.description: Indicates TX Rate(Kbit/sec) of the specifed port.Value 1024000 means no limit.

swL2QOSBandwidthRadiusRxRate.name: swL2QOSBandwidthRadiusRxRate
swL2QOSBandwidthRadiusRxRate.description: The RxRate value comes from RADIUS server, If an 802.1X port is authenticated, this value will overwrites the locally configured RxRate.

swL2QOSBandwidthRadiusTxRate.name: swL2QOSBandwidthRadiusTxRate
swL2QOSBandwidthRadiusTxRate.description: The TxRate value comes from RADIUS server, If an 802.1X port is authenticated, this value will overwrites the locally configured TxRate.

swL2QOSSchedulingEntry.name: swL2QOSSchedulingEntry
swL2QOSSchedulingEntry.description: A list of information contained in swL2QOSSchedulingTable.

swL2QOSSchedulingMechanismCtrl.name: swL2QOSSchedulingMechanismCtrl
swL2QOSSchedulingMechanismCtrl.description: This object can control QOS scheduling Mechanism.

swL2QOS8021pUserPriorityEntry.name: swL2QOS8021pUserPriorityEntry
swL2QOS8021pUserPriorityEntry.description: A list of information contained in swL2QOS8021pUserPriorityTable.

swL2QOS8021pUserPriorityClass.name: swL2QOS8021pUserPriorityClass
swL2QOS8021pUserPriorityClass.description: The number of the switch's hardware priority queue. The switch has four hardware priority queues available. They are numbered between 0 (the lowest priority) and 3 (the highest priority).

swL2QOS8021pDefaultPriorityEntry.name: swL2QOS8021pDefaultPriorityEntry
swL2QOS8021pDefaultPriorityEntry.description: A list of information contained in swL2QOS8021pDefaultPriorityTable.

swL2QOS8021pDefaultPriority.name: swL2QOS8021pDefaultPriority
swL2QOS8021pDefaultPriority.description: The priority value to assign to untagged packets received by the switch ports on the switch..

swL2QOS8021pRadiusPriority.name: swL2QOS8021pRadiusPriority
swL2QOS8021pRadiusPriority.description: The value of 802.1p comes from RADIUS server. If an 802.1X port is authenticated, this value will overwrite the local configured value.

swPortTrunkMaxPortMembers.name: swPortTrunkMaxPortMembers
swPortTrunkMaxPortMembers.description: The max number of ports allowed in a trunk.

swPortTrunkTable.name: swPortTrunkTable
swPortTrunkTable.description: This table specifies the port membership for each logical link.

swPortTrunkEntry.name: swPortTrunkEntry
swPortTrunkEntry.description: A list of information specifies which ports group form a single logical link.

swPortTrunkIndex.name: swPortTrunkIndex
swPortTrunkIndex.description: The index of logical port trunk.

swPortTrunkMasterPort.name: swPortTrunkMasterPort
swPortTrunkMasterPort.description: The object indicates the master port number of the port trunk entry.The first port of the trunk is implicitly configured to be the master logical port.When using Port Trunk, you can not configure the other ports of the group except the master port. Their configuration must be same as the master port (e.g. speed, duplex, enabled/disabled, flow control, and so on).

swPortTrunkPortList.name: swPortTrunkPortList
swPortTrunkPortList.description: Indicate member ports of a logical trunk.

swPortTrunkType.name: swPortTrunkType
swPortTrunkType.description: This object indicates the type of this entry.

swPortTrunkActivePort.name: swPortTrunkActivePort
swPortTrunkActivePort.description: This object indicates the active ports of this entry.

swPortTrunkState.name: swPortTrunkState
swPortTrunkState.description: This object indicates the status of this entry. when the state is CreatAndGo(4),the type of trunk is static(1); when the state is CreatAndWait(5),the type of trunk is lacp(2).

swPortTrunkFloodingPort.name: swPortTrunkFloodingPort
swPortTrunkFloodingPort.description: The flooding port of every trunk.

swL2TrunkAlgorithm.name: swL2TrunkAlgorithm
swL2TrunkAlgorithm.description: This object configures to part of the packet examined by the switch when selecting the egress port for transmitting load-sharing data.

swL2TrunkLACPPortTable.name: swL2TrunkLACPPortTable
swL2TrunkLACPPortTable.description: This table specifys which ports group a set of ports(up to 8) into a single logical link.

swL2TrunkLACPPortEntry.name: swL2TrunkLACPPortEntry
swL2TrunkLACPPortEntry.description: A list of information specifies which ports group a set of ports(up to 8) into a single logical link.

swL2TrunkLACPPortIndex.name: swL2TrunkLACPPortIndex
swL2TrunkLACPPortIndex.description: The index of logical port lacp.

swL2TrunkLACPPortState.name: swL2TrunkLACPPortState
swL2TrunkLACPPortState.description: The state of logical port lacp.

swL2TrunkVLANTable.name: swL2TrunkVLANTable
swL2TrunkVLANTable.description: This table is used to manage the VLAN trunking feature of the device.

swL2TrunkVLANEntry.name: swL2TrunkVLANEntry
swL2TrunkVLANEntry.description: This object is used to configure the VLAN trunking settings for each port.

swL2TrunkVLANPort.name: swL2TrunkVLANPort
swL2TrunkVLANPort.description: This object indicates the port being configured.

swL2TrunkVLANState.name: swL2TrunkVLANState
swL2TrunkVLANState.description: The state of the logical port LACP.

swPortMirrorRxPortList.name: swPortMirrorRxPortList
swPortMirrorRxPortList.description: This object indicates the Rx port list of ports to be sniffed.

swPortMirrorTxPortList.name: swPortMirrorTxPortList
swPortMirrorTxPortList.description: This object indicates the Tx port list of ports to be sniffed.

swPortMirrorTargetPort.name: swPortMirrorTargetPort
swPortMirrorTargetPort.description: This object indicates switch which port will sniff another port. A trunk port member cannot be configured as a target Snooping port. The port number is the sequential (logical) number which is also applied to bridge MIB, etc.

swPortMirrorState.name: swPortMirrorState
swPortMirrorState.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swL2IGMPMaxSupportedVlans.name: swL2IGMPMaxSupportedVlans
swL2IGMPMaxSupportedVlans.description: Maximum number of Vlans in the layer 2 IGMP control table (swL2IGMPCtrlTable).

swL2IGMPMaxIpGroupNumPerVlan.name: swL2IGMPMaxIpGroupNumPerVlan
swL2IGMPMaxIpGroupNumPerVlan.description: Maximum number of multicast ip group per Vlan in the layer 2 IGMP information table (swL2IGMPQueryInfoTable).

swL2IGMPCtrlTable.name: swL2IGMPCtrlTable
swL2IGMPCtrlTable.description: The table controls the Vlan's IGMP function. Its scale depends on current VLAN state (swL2VlanInfoStatus). If VLAN is disabled mode, there is only one entry in the table, with index 1. If VLAN is in Port-Base or 802.1q mode, the number of entries can be up to 12, with index range from 1 to 12.

swL2IGMPCtrlEntry.name: swL2IGMPCtrlEntry
swL2IGMPCtrlEntry.description: The entry in IGMP control table (swL2IGMPCtrlTable). The entry is effective only when IGMP capture switch (swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping) is enabled.

swL2IGMPCtrlVid.name: swL2IGMPCtrlVid
swL2IGMPCtrlVid.description: This object indicates the IGMP control entry's VLAN id. If VLAN is disabled, the Vid is always 0 and cannot be changed by management users. If VLAN is in Port-Base mode, the Vid is arranged from 1 to 12, fixed form. If VLAN is in 802.1q mode, the Vid setting can vary from 1 to 4094 by management user, and the Vid in each entry must be unique in the IGMP Control Table.

swL2IGMPQueryInterval.name: swL2IGMPQueryInterval
swL2IGMPQueryInterval.description: The frequency at which IGMP Host-Query packets are transmitted on this switch.

swL2IGMPMaxResponseTime.name: swL2IGMPMaxResponseTime
swL2IGMPMaxResponseTime.description: The maximum query response time on this switch.

swL2IGMPRobustness.name: swL2IGMPRobustness
swL2IGMPRobustness.description: The Robustness Variable allows tuning for the expected packet loss on a subnet. If a subnet is expected to be lossy, the Robustness Variable may be increased. IGMP is robust to (Robustness Variable-1) packet losses.

swL2IGMPLastMemberQueryInterval.name: swL2IGMPLastMemberQueryInterval
swL2IGMPLastMemberQueryInterval.description: The Last Member Query Interval is the Max Response Time inserted into Group-Specific Queries sent in response to Leave Group messages, and is also the amount of time between Group-Specific Query messages.

swL2IGMPHostTimeout.name: swL2IGMPHostTimeout
swL2IGMPHostTimeout.description: The timer value for sending IGMP query packet when none was sent by the host in the LAN. The timer works in per-VLAN basis. Our device will be activated to send the query message if the timer is expired. Please reference RFC2236-1997.

swL2IGMPRouteTimeout.name: swL2IGMPRouteTimeout
swL2IGMPRouteTimeout.description: The Router Timeout is how long a host must wait after hearing a Query before it may send any IGMPv2 messages.

swL2IGMPLeaveTimer.name: swL2IGMPLeaveTimer
swL2IGMPLeaveTimer.description: When a querier receives a Leave Group message for a group that has group members on the reception interface, it sends Group-Specific Queries every swL2IGMPLeaveTimer to the group being left.

swL2IGMPQueryState.name: swL2IGMPQueryState
swL2IGMPQueryState.description: This object decide the IGMP query enabled or disabled.

swL2IGMPCurrentState.name: swL2IGMPCurrentState
swL2IGMPCurrentState.description: This object indicates the current IGMP query state.

swL2IGMPCtrlState.name: swL2IGMPCtrlState
swL2IGMPCtrlState.description: This object indicates the status of this entry. other(1) - this entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so are different from each of the following values. disable(2) - IGMP funtion is disabled for this entry. enable(3) - IGMP funtion is enabled for this entry.

swL2IGMPQueryInfoTable.name: swL2IGMPQueryInfoTable
swL2IGMPQueryInfoTable.description: The table contains the number current IGMP query packets which is captured by this device, as well as the IGMP query packets sent by the device.

swL2IGMPQueryInfoEntry.name: swL2IGMPQueryInfoEntry
swL2IGMPQueryInfoEntry.description: Information about current IGMP query information, provided that swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping and swL2IGMPCtrState of associated VLAN entry are all enabled.

swL2IGMPInfoVid.name: swL2IGMPInfoVid
swL2IGMPInfoVid.description: This object indicates the Vid of associated IGMP info table entry. It follows swL2IGMPCtrlVid in the associated entry of IGMP control table (swL2IGMPCtrlTable).

swL2IGMPInfoQueryCount.name: swL2IGMPInfoQueryCount
swL2IGMPInfoQueryCount.description: This object indicates the number of query packets received since the IGMP function enabled, in per-VLAN basis.

swL2IGMPInfoTxQueryCount.name: swL2IGMPInfoTxQueryCount
swL2IGMPInfoTxQueryCount.description: This object indicates the send count of IGMP query messages, in per-VLAN basis. In case of IGMP timer expiration, the switch sends IGMP query packets to related VLAN member ports and increment this object by 1.

swL2IGMPInfoTable.name: swL2IGMPInfoTable
swL2IGMPInfoTable.description: The table containing current IGMP information which captured by this device, provided that swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping and swL2IGMPCtrlState of associated VLAN entry are all enabled. Note that the priority of IGMP table entries is lower than Filtering Table, i.e. if there is a table hash collision between the entries of IGMP Table and Filtering Table inside the switch H/W address table, then Filtering Table entry overwrite the colliding entry of IGMP Table. See swL2FilterMgmt description also.

swL2IGMPInfoEntry.name: swL2IGMPInfoEntry
swL2IGMPInfoEntry.description: Information about current IGMP information which captured by this device, provided that swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping and swL2IGMPCtrlState of associated VLAN entry are all enabled.

swL2IGMPVid.name: swL2IGMPVid
swL2IGMPVid.description: This object indicates the Vid of individual IGMP table entry. It shows the Vid of IGMP report information captured on network.

swL2IGMPGroupIpAddr.name: swL2IGMPGroupIpAddr
swL2IGMPGroupIpAddr.description: This object is identify group ip address which is captured from IGMP packet, in per-Vlan basis.

swL2IGMPMacAddr.name: swL2IGMPMacAddr
swL2IGMPMacAddr.description: This object is identify mac address which is corresponding to swL2IGMPGroupIpAddr, in per-Vlan basis.

swL2IGMPPortMap.name: swL2IGMPPortMap
swL2IGMPPortMap.description: This object indicates which ports are belong to the same multicast group, in per-Vlan basis. Each multicast group has a octect string to indicate with port map. The most significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus, each port of the switch is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is included in the set of ports; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0'(Note that the setting of the bit corresponding to the port from which a frame is received is irrelevant). The 4 octets is represent one unit port according its logic port. If the unit less 32 port, the other port don't care just fill zero.

swL2IGMPIpGroupReportCount.name: swL2IGMPIpGroupReportCount
swL2IGMPIpGroupReportCount.description: This object indicate how much report packet was receive by our device corresponding with this entry from IGMP function enabled, in per-Vlan basis.

swL2IGMPRouterPortTable.name: swL2IGMPRouterPortTable
swL2IGMPRouterPortTable.description: The information of the router port table.

swL2IGMPRouterPortVlanid.name: swL2IGMPRouterPortVlanid
swL2IGMPRouterPortVlanid.description: This object indicates the vlan id of the router port entry.

swL2IGMPRouterPortVlanName.name: swL2IGMPRouterPortVlanName
swL2IGMPRouterPortVlanName.description: This object indicates the vlan name of the router port entry.

swL2IGMPRouterPortStaticPortList.name: swL2IGMPRouterPortStaticPortList
swL2IGMPRouterPortStaticPortList.description: This object indicate the static portlist of the router port entry.

swL2IGMPRouterPortDynamicPortList.name: swL2IGMPRouterPortDynamicPortList
swL2IGMPRouterPortDynamicPortList.description: This object indicate the dynamic portlist of the router port entry.

swL2IGMPRouterPortForbiddenPortList.name: swL2IGMPRouterPortForbiddenPortList
swL2IGMPRouterPortForbiddenPortList.description: This object indicate the forbidden portlist of the router port entry.

swL2IGMPAccessAuthTable.name: swL2IGMPAccessAuthTable
swL2IGMPAccessAuthTable.description: This table is used to manage the IGMP Access Authentication configurations of the device.

swL2IGMPAccessAuthEntry.name: swL2IGMPAccessAuthEntry
swL2IGMPAccessAuthEntry.description: A list of manageable entities for IGMP Access Authentication. The configuration is done per port.

swL2IGMPAccessAuthPort.name: swL2IGMPAccessAuthPort
swL2IGMPAccessAuthPort.description: The index of the swL2IGMPAccessAuthTable. This object corresponds to the port being configured.

swL2IGMPAccessAuthState.name: swL2IGMPAccessAuthState
swL2IGMPAccessAuthState.description: This object denotes the status of IGMP Access Authentication of the port.

swL2TrafficCtrlTable.name: swL2TrafficCtrlTable
swL2TrafficCtrlTable.description: This table specifys the storm traffic control configuration.

swL2TrafficCtrlEntry.name: swL2TrafficCtrlEntry
swL2TrafficCtrlEntry.description: A list of information specifies the storm traffic control configuration.

swL2TrafficCtrlGroupIndex.name: swL2TrafficCtrlGroupIndex
swL2TrafficCtrlGroupIndex.description: The index of logical port trunk. The trunk group number depend on the existence of unit and module.

swL2TrafficCtrlUnitIndex.name: swL2TrafficCtrlUnitIndex
swL2TrafficCtrlUnitIndex.description: Indicates ID of the unit in the device

swL2TrafficCtrlBMStromthreshold.name: swL2TrafficCtrlBMStromthreshold
swL2TrafficCtrlBMStromthreshold.description: This object to decide how much thousand packets per second broadcast/multicast (depend on swL2TrafficCtrlBcastStromCtrl, swL2TrafficCtrlMcastStromCtrl or swL2TrafficCtrlUcastStromCtrl objects whether is enabled) will active storm control. Whenever a port reaches its configured amount of packets in the one second time interval, the device will start dropping that type of packet, until the time interval has expired. Once the time interval has expired, the device will start forwarding that type of packet.

swL2TrafficCtrlBcastStromCtrl.name: swL2TrafficCtrlBcastStromCtrl
swL2TrafficCtrlBcastStromCtrl.description: This object indicates broadcast storm control function is enabled or disabled.

swL2TrafficCtrlMcastStromCtrl.name: swL2TrafficCtrlMcastStromCtrl
swL2TrafficCtrlMcastStromCtrl.description: This object indicates multicast storm control function is enabled or disabled.

swL2TrafficCtrlUcastStromCtrl.name: swL2TrafficCtrlUcastStromCtrl
swL2TrafficCtrlUcastStromCtrl.description: This object indicates destination lookup fail function is enabled or disabled.

swL2TrafficSegTable.name: swL2TrafficSegTable
swL2TrafficSegTable.description: This table specifys the port just can forward traffic to the specific port list.

swL2TrafficSegEntry.name: swL2TrafficSegEntry
swL2TrafficSegEntry.description: A list of information specifies the port with its traffic forward list.

swL2TrafficSegPort.name: swL2TrafficSegPort
swL2TrafficSegPort.description: The port number of the logical port.

swL2TrafficSegForwardPorts.name: swL2TrafficSegForwardPorts
swL2TrafficSegForwardPorts.description: The port list that the specific port can forward traffic.

swL2PortSecurityControlTable.name: swL2PortSecurityControlTable
swL2PortSecurityControlTable.description: port security feature which controls the address leaning capability and the traffic forwarding decision. Each port can have this function enabled or disabled. When it is enabled and a number is given said N, which allows N addresses to be learned at this port, the first N learned addresses are locked at this port as static entry. When the learned addresses number reach N, any coming packet with not learned source addresses are discarded (e.g. dropped) and no more new addresses can be learned at this port.

swL2PortSecurityControlEntry.name: swL2PortSecurityControlEntry
swL2PortSecurityControlEntry.description: A list of information contained in swL2PortSecurityControlTable.

swL2PortSecurityPortIndex.name: swL2PortSecurityPortIndex
swL2PortSecurityPortIndex.description: Indicates the secured port to lock address learning.

swL2PortSecurityMaxLernAddr.name: swL2PortSecurityMaxLernAddr
swL2PortSecurityMaxLernAddr.description: Indicates allowable number of addresses to be learned at this port.

swL2PortSecurityMode.name: swL2PortSecurityMode
swL2PortSecurityMode.description: Indicates the mode of locking address. In deleteOnTimeout(3) mode - the locked addresses can be aged out after aging timer expire. In this mode, when the locked address is aged out, the number of address can be learned has to be increased by one. In deleteOnReset(4) mode - never age out the locked addresses unless restart the system to prevent from port movement or intrusion.

swL2PortSecurityAdmState.name: swL2PortSecurityAdmState
swL2PortSecurityAdmState.description: Indicates administration state of locking address.

swL2PortSecurityTrapLogState.name: swL2PortSecurityTrapLogState
swL2PortSecurityTrapLogState.description: when enable(2),whenever there's a new MAC that violates the pre-defined port security configuration, trap will be sent out and the relevant information will be logged in system.

swL2StpForwardBPDU.name: swL2StpForwardBPDU
swL2StpForwardBPDU.description: Indicates whether flooding BPDU packets when STP is disabled on device

swL2StpLbd.name: swL2StpLbd
swL2StpLbd.description: Indicates whether STP loop-back prevent on the device is turned on

swL2StpLbdRecoverTime.name: swL2StpLbdRecoverTime
swL2StpLbdRecoverTime.description: The period of time on which STP module keeps checking the BPDU loop status, to configure swL2StpLbdRecoverTime as 0 disables automatically recover

swL2StpPortTable.name: swL2StpPortTable
swL2StpPortTable.description: A table that contains port-specific information for the Spanning Tree Protocol.

swL2StpPortEntry.name: swL2StpPortEntry
swL2StpPortEntry.description: A list of information maintained by every port about the Spanning Tree Protocol state for that port.

swL2StpPort.name: swL2StpPort
swL2StpPort.description: The port number of the port for this entry.

swL2StpPortLbd.name: swL2StpPortLbd
swL2StpPortLbd.description: The enabled/disabled status is used to Loop-back prevention attached to this port.

swL2StpPortStatus.name: swL2StpPortStatus
swL2StpPortStatus.description: When the port Enable state is enabled, the port's current state as defined by application of the Spanning Tree Protocol. If the PortEnable is disabled, the the port status will be no-stp-enabled(7). If the port is in error disabled status, the port status will be err-disabled(8)

swL2StpPortRole.name: swL2StpPortRole
swL2StpPortRole.description: When the port Enable state is enabled, the port's current port role as defined by application of the Spanning Tree Protocol. If the Port Enable state is disabled, the the port role will be nonstp(7). If the port is in loop-back status, the port role will be loopback(8)

swL2StpPortFBPDU.name: swL2StpPortFBPDU
swL2StpPortFBPDU.description: The enabled/disabled status is used to BPDU Filtering attached to this port.

swL2StpPortLinkState.name: swL2StpPortLinkState
swL2StpPortLinkState.description: This object indicates the stp port speed and duplex mode.

swL2StpPortProtocolMigration.name: swL2StpPortProtocolMigration
swL2StpPortProtocolMigration.description: When operating in RSTP (version 2) mode, writing TRUE(1) to this object forces this port to transmit RSTP BPDUs. Any other operation on this object has no effect and it always returns FALSE(2) when read.

swL2StpPortAdminEdgePort.name: swL2StpPortAdminEdgePort
swL2StpPortAdminEdgePort.description: The administrative value of the Edge Port parameter. A value of TRUE(0) indicates that this port should be assumed as an edge-port and a value of FALSE(1) indicates that this port should be assumed as a non-edge-port.

swL2StpPortOperEdgePort.name: swL2StpPortOperEdgePort
swL2StpPortOperEdgePort.description: The operational value of the Edge Port parameter. The object is initialized to the value of swL2StpPortAdminEdgePort and is set FALSE on reception of a BPDU.

swL2StpPortAdminPointToPoint.name: swL2StpPortAdminPointToPoint
swL2StpPortAdminPointToPoint.description: The administrative point-to-point status of the LAN segment attached to this port. A value of forceTrue(0) indicates that this port should always be treated as if it is connected to a point-to-point link. A value of forceFalse(1) indicates that this port should be treated as having a shared media connection. A value of auto(2) indicates that this port is considered to have a point-to-point link if it is an Aggregator and all of its members are aggregatable, or if the MAC entity is configured for full duplex operation, either through auto-negotiation or by management means.

swL2StpPortOperPointToPoint.name: swL2StpPortOperPointToPoint
swL2StpPortOperPointToPoint.description: The operational point-to-point status of the LAN segment attached to this port. It indicates whether a port is considered to have a point-to-point connection or not. The value is determined by management or by auto-detection, as described in the swL2StpPortAdminPointToPoint object.

swL2StpPortAdminPathCost.name: swL2StpPortAdminPathCost
swL2StpPortAdminPathCost.description: The administratively assigned value for the contribution of this port to the path cost of paths towards the spanning tree root. Writing a value of '0' assigns the automatically calculated default Path Cost value to the port. If the default Path Cost is being used, this object returns '0' when read. This complements the object swL2StpPortPathCost, which returns the operational value of the path cost. Issue No.: 3250R2-077 As USE_RSTP is 1:enabled, swL2StpPortPathCost is forced to be read-only. configuration via swL2StpPortAdminPathCost. According 802.1w, value range of swL2StpPortAdminPathCost would be expanded. the former value range is (0..65535), the new is (0..200000000).

swL2StpPortPriority.name: swL2StpPortPriority
swL2StpPortPriority.description: The value of the priority field which is contained in the first (in network byte order) octet of the (2 octet long) Port ID. The other octet of the Port ID is given by the value of swL2StpPort.

swL2STPPortState.name: swL2STPPortState
swL2STPPortState.description: The enabled/disabled status is usedoop-back prevention attached to this port.

swL2StpPortRestrictedRole.name: swL2StpPortRestrictedRole
swL2StpPortRestrictedRole.description: If TRUE causes the port not to be selected as Root Port, even it has the best spanning tree priotiry vector.

swL2StpPortRestrictedTCN.name: swL2StpPortRestrictedTCN
swL2StpPortRestrictedTCN.description: If TRUE causes the port not to propagate received topology change notifications and topology changes to other Ports.

swL2CosPriorityTable.name: swL2CosPriorityTable
swL2CosPriorityTable.description: Used to show and config per port priority-based QoS features on the switch

swL2CosPriorityEntry.description: A list of information contained in swL2CosPriorityTable.

swL2CosPriorityPort.name: swL2CosPriorityPort
swL2CosPriorityPort.description: The port number of CoS Priority.

swL2CosPriorityEtherPRI.name: swL2CosPriorityEtherPRI
swL2CosPriorityEtherPRI.description: Enable Ethernet frame based priority. When set ether8021p(2), enable 802.1p QoS; When set macBase(3), enable MAC-based QoS; When set disable(1), disable Ethernet frame based priority.

swL2CosPriorityIpPRI.name: swL2CosPriorityIpPRI
swL2CosPriorityIpPRI.description: Enable IP priority QoS. When set tos(2), enable TOS based QoS; When set dscp(3), enable DSCP based QoS; When set disable(1), disable IP priority QoS.

swL2CosPriorityNone.name: swL2CosPriorityNone
swL2CosPriorityNone.description: when read,it always return invalid(2); when write valid(1),it disables all priority in this table.

swL2CosPortPRITable.name: swL2CosPortPRITable
swL2CosPortPRITable.description: Used to show port-to-class mappings and map specific port to one of the hardware queues available on the switch.

swL2CosPortPRIEntry.name: swL2CosPortPRIEntry
swL2CosPortPRIEntry.description: A list of information contained in swL2CosPortPRITable.

swL2CosPortPRIClass.name: swL2CosPortPRIClass
swL2CosPortPRIClass.description: The number of the switch's hardware priority queue. The switch has 4 hardware priority queues available. They are numbered between 0 (the lowest priority queue) and 3 (the highest priority queue). If you want to set, You must have administrator privileges. And you can set value only 0 or 3,you can't set value 1 or 2.

swL2CosMacBasePRITable.name: swL2CosMacBasePRITable
swL2CosMacBasePRITable.description: Used to show MAC priority map to traffic class and map the destination MAC address in incoming packet to one of the hardware queues available on the switch.

swL2CosMacBasePRIEntry.name: swL2CosMacBasePRIEntry
swL2CosMacBasePRIEntry.description: A list of information contained in swL2CosMacBasePRITable.

swL2CosMacBasePRIClass.name: swL2CosMacBasePRIClass
swL2CosMacBasePRIClass.description: The number of the switch's hardware priority queue. The switch has 4 hardware priority queues available. They are numbered between 0 (the lowest priority queue) and 3 (the highest priority queue). If you want to set, You must have administrator privileges.

swL2CosTosPRITable.name: swL2CosTosPRITable
swL2CosTosPRITable.description: Used to show TOS value to traffic class mapping and map the TOS value in the IP header of incoming packet to one of the four hardware queues available on the switch.

swL2CosTosPRIEntry.name: swL2CosTosPRIEntry
swL2CosTosPRIEntry.description: A list of information contained in swL2CosTosPRITable.

swL2CosTosPRIClass.name: swL2CosTosPRIClass
swL2CosTosPRIClass.description: The number of the switch's hardware priority queue. The switch has 4 hardware priority queues available. They are numbered between 0 (the lowest priority queue) and 3 (the highest priority queue). If you want to set, You must have administrator privileges.

swL2CosDscpPRITable.name: swL2CosDscpPRITable
swL2CosDscpPRITable.description: Used to show DSCP value to traffic class mapping and map the DSCP value in the IP header of incoming packet to one of the hardware queues available on the switch.

swL2CosDscpPRIEntry.name: swL2CosDscpPRIEntry
swL2CosDscpPRIEntry.description: A list of information contained in swL2CosDscpPRITable.

swL2CosDscpPRIClass.name: swL2CosDscpPRIClass
swL2CosDscpPRIClass.description: The number of the switch's hardware priority queue. The switch has 4 hardware priority queues available. They are numbered between 0 (the lowest priority queue) and 3 (the highest priority queue). If you want to set, You must have administrator privileges.
